data.title: Australian Cricketers' Association
data.meta_description: The ACA is the collective and representative voice of past and present male and female elite domestic and international cricketers in Australia.
data.text:
ACA General Manager - Past Players Clea Smith has praised the contributions to cricket of three ACA members, Jeff Kowalick, Peter Davies and Tony Benneworth, after their passing in recent weeks.

"Everyone at the ACA, from the staff to the membership, were saddened to learn of the passing of three of our members in recent times" Smith said.

"The three men contributed heavily to domestic and Premier cricket and will be sorely missed.

"The ACA passes on it's sincere condoloences to the Kowalick, Davies and Benneworth families," Smith concluded.

Peter John Davies played six First Class games for Victoria and was a Life Member of the Richmond (now Monash Tigers) Cricket Club.
